{{Frame
|FrameNet frame=Planting
|Comments=Please note: there exist the following frames: Plants, Weeds, Tending to plants, Plant life cycle. Add LUs accordingly.


This frame assumes a knowledge system that distinguishes between animal and plant life, or sentient and non-sentient living entities. Our Linnean taxonomy of plants also structures to a great extent our plant-life categorization, so for the purpose of metaphor mapping, some plants will be more plant-like than others (e.g. flowers more-so than seaweed), and the selective mapping will reflect this categorization.
